sentence: Under Armour, Inc.UA , the developer, marketer and distributor of branded performance apparel, footwear, and accessories, is slated to report fourth-quarter 2015 results on Jan 28.
The big question facing investors is, whether the company will be able to deliver a positive earnings surprise in the quarter to be reported.
In the trailing four quarters, the company outperformed the Zacks Consensus Estimate by an average of 11.2%.
Let's see how things are shaping up for this announcement.
Our proven model does not conclusively show that Under Armour is likely to beat earnings estimates this quarter.
This is because a stock needs to have both a positive Earnings ESP and a Zacks Rank #1, 2 or 3 for this to happen.
Under Armour has an Earnings ESP of -4.26% as the Most Accurate estimate stands at 45 cents, while the Zacks Consensus Estimate is pegged at 47 cents.
Moreover, the company carries a Zacks Rank #4 (Sell).
We caution against stocks with a Zacks Rank #4 or 5 (Sell-rated stocks) going into the earnings announcement, especially when the company is seeing negative estimate revisions.

Management had earlier highlighted that costs related to the acquisitions of two new Connected Fitness businesses and softening of foreign currencies against the U.S. dollar, will exert pressure on operating margin within international businesses.

At its last earnings release, Under Armour cautioned that gross margin rate may contract during the fourth quarter due to foreign currency headwinds, increase in freight costs and a higher mix of footwear revenues.
Analysts also pointed out that the company is struggling to maintain its share of the apparel market.
All these factors may weigh upon Under Armour's performance in the quarter to be reported.

Here are some companies you may want to consider as our model shows that these have the right combination of elements to post an earnings beat:

Express Inc. EXPR has an Earnings ESP of +1.56% and a Zacks Rank #1 (Strong Buy).
Foot Locker, Inc. FL has an Earnings ESP of +0.89% and a Zacks Rank #2 (Buy).
The Home Depot, Inc. HD has an Earnings ESP of +0.91% and a Zacks Rank #2.
